# Development Setup

## Purpose

The purpose of this document is to define the development environment, tools, technologies, and setup process required for building the Master Portfolio project.

This document serves as a reference for setting up the project from scratch and helps maintain consistency throughout the development lifecycle.

---

# Development Environment

## Operating System

Current Development Environment:

* Windows 11

The project should remain platform-independent and work on Windows, Linux, and macOS.

---

## Code Editor

### Visual Studio Code

Purpose:

Primary code editor for development.

Reasons for Selection:

* Lightweight
* Large extension ecosystem
* Excellent React support
* Git integration
* Terminal integration

Official Responsibilities:

* Writing code
* Debugging
* Version control management
* Project navigation

---

# Required Software

## Node.js

Purpose:

JavaScript runtime used to execute development tools and build processes.

Responsibilities:

* Package management support
* Development server execution
* Build generation

Verification Command:

```bash
node -v
```

Expected Result:

Displays installed Node.js version.

---

## npm

Purpose:

Package manager used to install and manage project dependencies.

Responsibilities:

* Dependency installation
* Script execution
* Package updates

Verification Command:

```bash
npm -v
```

Expected Result:

Displays installed npm version.

---

## Git

Purpose:

Version control system used to track project changes.

Responsibilities:

* Source code tracking
* Commit history management
* Branch management
* Collaboration

Verification Command:

```bash
git --version
```

Expected Result:

Displays installed Git version.

---

